## Detailed Implementation Plan: 4 Audit Findings

### Execution Order

The four findings have dependencies that dictate sequencing. Finding D (duration precision) is a surgical one-line fix with no dependencies and should go first. Finding A (booking approval) is the largest change but self-contained. Finding B (terms acceptance) requires a new migration and new files. Finding C (media validation) touches the course subsystem independently. The recommended order is: **D, A, B, C**.

---

### Phase 1: Finding D -- Booking Duration Precision

**Problem**: `booking_service.rs` line 106 uses `num_hours()` which truncates to integer. A 4h01m booking passes a 4h max check because `num_hours()` returns 4. The same bug exists on line 198 (reschedule path).

